						               													<description>From the Publisher: Una Notte da Lupi is a fast game full of tension.&amp;#10;Each player gets a hidden role: Werewolf, Seer, a harmless Farmer or another of the odd villagers with special powers.&amp;#10;Werewolves try to muddy the waters while villagers try to find out their identities. Who will win?&amp;#10;Whatever is your role, be on the watch and don't trust to easily on what other players say!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The following roles did not exist in One Night Werewolf, but do exist in both One Night Ultimate Werewolf as well as dV Gicochi&amp;rsquo;s Una Notte da Lupi.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Troublemaker: This is almost exactly the same as in One Night Ultimate Werewolf (Una Notte da Lupi has the limitation that the switched characters are limited to the players to the left and right of the Troublemaker)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Masons: This is exactly the same as the Masons One Night Ultimate Werewolf&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Miteane: This is exactly the same as the Minion in One Night Ultimate Werewolf&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sorcerer&amp;rsquo;s Apprentice: This appears to be the same as the Alpha Wolf character from One Night Ultimate Werewolf Daybreak (the translation is not very good)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Werewolf Penguin: This is exactly the same as the Tanner for One Night Ultimate Werewolf&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mortovio: This appears to be the Hunter from One Night Ultimate Werewolf (again, there are a few issues with the translation)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition, Una Notte da Lupi provides tokens that correspond to the roles used in the game, something that One Night Ultimate Werewolf has, and One Night Werewolf does not.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
